Enum.name: EDBG_0
Enum.description: When in debug mode, the DMA continues to operate.

Enum.name: EDBG_1
Enum.description: When in debug mode, the DMA stalls the start of a new channel. Executing channels are allowed to complete. Channel execution resumes when the system exits debug mode or the EDBG bit is cleared.

Enum.name: ERCA_0
Enum.description: Fixed priority arbitration is used for channel selection .

Enum.name: ERCA_1
Enum.description: Round robin arbitration is used for channel selection .

Enum.name: HOE_0
Enum.description: Normal operation

Enum.name: HOE_1
Enum.description: Any error causes the HALT bit to set. Subsequently, all service requests are ignored until the HALT bit is cleared.

Enum.name: HALT_0
Enum.description: Normal operation

Enum.name: HALT_1
Enum.description: Stall the start of any new channels. Executing channels are allowed to complete. Channel execution resumes when this bit is cleared.

Enum.name: CLM_0
Enum.description: A minor loop channel link made to itself goes through channel arbitration before being activated again.

Enum.name: CLM_1
Enum.description: A minor loop channel link made to itself does not go through channel arbitration before being activated again. Upon minor loop completion, the channel activates again if that channel has a minor loop channel link enabled and the link channel is itself. This effectively applies the minor loop offsets and restarts the next minor loop.

Enum.name: EMLM_0
Enum.description: Disabled. TCDn.word2 is defined as a 32-bit NBYTES field.

Enum.name: EMLM_1
Enum.description: Enabled. TCDn.word2 is redefined to include individual enable fields, an offset field, and the NBYTES field. The individual enable fields allow the minor loop offset to be applied to the source address, the destination address, or both. The NBYTES field is reduced when either offset is enabled.

Enum.name: ECX_0
Enum.description: Normal operation

Enum.name: ECX_1
Enum.description: Cancel the remaining data transfer in the same fashion as the CX bit. Stop the executing channel and force the minor loop to finish. The cancel takes effect after the last write of the current read/write sequence. The ECX bit clears itself after the cancel is honored. In addition to cancelling the transfer, ECX treats the cancel as an error condition, thus updating the Error Status register (DMAx_ES) and generating an optional error interrupt.

Enum.name: CX_0
Enum.description: Normal operation

Enum.name: CX_1
Enum.description: Cancel the remaining data transfer. Stop the executing channel and force the minor loop to finish. The cancel takes effect after the last write of the current read/write sequence. The CX bit clears itself after the cancel has been honored. This cancel retires the channel normally as if the minor loop was completed.

Enum.name: ACTIVE_0
Enum.description: eDMA is idle.

Enum.name: ACTIVE_1
Enum.description: eDMA is executing a channel.

Enum.name: DBE_0
Enum.description: No destination bus error

Enum.name: DBE_1
Enum.description: The last recorded error was a bus error on a destination write

Enum.name: SBE_0
Enum.description: No source bus error

Enum.name: SBE_1
Enum.description: The last recorded error was a bus error on a source read

Enum.name: SGE_0
Enum.description: No scatter/gather configuration error

Enum.name: SGE_1
Enum.description: The last recorded error was a configuration error detected in the TCDn_DLASTSGA field. This field is checked at the beginning of a scatter/gather operation after major loop completion if TCDn_CSR[ESG] is enabled. TCDn_DLASTSGA is not on a 32 byte boundary.

Enum.name: NCE_0
Enum.description: No NBYTES/CITER configuration error

Enum.name: NCE_1
Enum.description: The last recorded error was a configuration error detected in the TCDn_NBYTES or TCDn_CITER fields. TCDn_NBYTES is not a multiple of TCDn_ATTR[SSIZE] and TCDn_ATTR[DSIZE], or TCDn_CITER[CITER] is equal to zero, or TCDn_CITER[ELINK] is not equal to TCDn_BITER[ELINK]

Enum.name: DOE_0
Enum.description: No destination offset configuration error

Enum.name: DOE_1
Enum.description: The last recorded error was a configuration error detected in the TCDn_DOFF field. TCDn_DOFF is inconsistent with TCDn_ATTR[DSIZE].

Enum.name: DAE_0
Enum.description: No destination address configuration error

Enum.name: DAE_1
Enum.description: The last recorded error was a configuration error detected in the TCDn_DADDR field. TCDn_DADDR is inconsistent with TCDn_ATTR[DSIZE].

Enum.name: SOE_0
Enum.description: No source offset configuration error

Enum.name: SOE_1

Enum.name: SMOD_0
Enum.description: Source address modulo feature is disabled

Enum.name: SMOD_1
Enum.description: This value defines a specific address range specified to be the value after SADDR + SOFF calculation is performed on the original register value. Setting this field provides the ability to implement a circular data queue easily. For data queues requiring power-of-2 size bytes, the queue should start at a 0-modulo-size address and the SMOD field should be set to the appropriate value for the queue, freezing the desired number of upper address bits. The value programmed into this field specifies the number of lower address bits allowed to change. For a circular queue application, the SOFF is typically set to the transfer size to implement post-increment addressing with the SMOD function constraining the addresses to a 0-modulo-size range.

Enum.name: SMOD_0
Enum.description: Source address modulo feature is disabled

Enum.name: SMOD_1
Enum.description: This value defines a specific address range specified to be the value after SADDR + SOFF calculation is performed on the original register value. Setting this field provides the ability to implement a circular data queue easily. For data queues requiring power-of-2 size bytes, the queue should start at a 0-modulo-size address and the SMOD field should be set to the appropriate value for the queue, freezing the desired number of upper address bits. The value programmed into this field specifies the number of lower address bits allowed to change. For a circular queue application, the SOFF is typically set to the transfer size to implement post-increment addressing with the SMOD function constraining the addresses to a 0-modulo-size range.

Enum.name: SMOD_0
Enum.description: Source address modulo feature is disabled

Enum.name: SMOD_1
Enum.description: This value defines a specific address range specified to be the value after SADDR + SOFF calculation is performed on the original register value. Setting this field provides the ability to implement a circular data queue easily. For data queues requiring power-of-2 size bytes, the queue should start at a 0-modulo-size address and the SMOD field should be set to the appropriate value for the queue, freezing the desired number of upper address bits. The value programmed into this field specifies the number of lower address bits allowed to change. For a circular queue application, the SOFF is typically set to the transfer size to implement post-increment addressing with the SMOD function constraining the addresses to a 0-modulo-size range.

Enum.name: SMOD_0
Enum.description: Source address modulo feature is disabled

Enum.name: SMOD_1
Enum.description: This value defines a specific address range specified to be the value after SADDR + SOFF calculation is performed on the original register value. Setting this field provides the ability to implement a circular data queue easily. For data queues requiring power-of-2 size bytes, the queue should start at a 0-modulo-size address and the SMOD field should be set to the appropriate value for the queue, freezing the desired number of upper address bits. The value programmed into this field specifies the number of lower address bits allowed to change. For a circular queue application, the SOFF is typically set to the transfer size to implement post-increment addressing with the SMOD function constraining the addresses to a 0-modulo-size range.

Enum.name: GROUP5_1
Enum.description: FB_CS3_B. You must also write 1b to CSCR[AA].

Enum.description: FB_BE_7_0_B. You must also write 1b to CSCR[AA].

Enum.name: V_0
Enum.description: Chip-select is invalid.

Enum.name: V_1
Enum.description: Chip-select is valid.

Enum.name: WP_0
Enum.description: Write accesses are allowed.

Enum.name: WP_1
Enum.description: Write accesses are not allowed. Attempting to write to the range of addresses for which the WP bit is set results in a bus error termination of the internal cycle and no external cycle.

Enum.name: BAM_0
Enum.description: The corresponding address bit in CSAR is used in the chip-select decode.

Enum.name: BAM_1
Enum.description: The corresponding address bit in CSAR is a don't care in the chip-select decode.

Enum.name: BSTW_0
Enum.description: Disabled. Data exceeding the specified port size is broken into individual, port-sized, non-burst writes. For example, a 32-bit write to an 8-bit port takes four byte writes.

Enum.name: BSTW_1
Enum.description: Enabled. Enables burst write of data larger than the specified port size, including 32-bit writes to 8- and 16-bit ports, 16-bit writes to 8-bit ports, and line writes to 8-, 16-, and 32-bit ports.

Enum.name: BSTR_0
Enum.description: Disabled. Data exceeding the specified port size is broken into individual, port-sized, non-burst reads. For example, a 32-bit read from an 8-bit port is broken into four 8-bit reads.

Enum.name: BSTR_1
Enum.description: Enabled. Enables data burst reads larger than the specified port size, including 32-bit reads from 8- and 16-bit ports, 16-bit reads from 8-bit ports, and line reads from 8-, 16-, and 32-bit ports.

Enum.name: BEM_0
Enum.description: FB_BE_B is asserted for data write only.

Enum.name: BEM_1
Enum.description: FB_BE_B is asserted for data read and write accesses.

Enum.description: Write accesses are not allowed. Attempting to write to the range of addresses for which the WP bit is set results in a bus error termination of the internal cycle and no external cycle.

Enum.name: BAM_0
Enum.description: The corresponding address bit in CSAR is used in the chip-select decode.

Enum.name: BAM_1
Enum.description: The corresponding address bit in CSAR is a don't care in the chip-select decode.

Enum.name: BSTW_0
Enum.description: Disabled. Data exceeding the specified port size is broken into individual, port-sized, non-burst writes. For example, a 32-bit write to an 8-bit port takes four byte writes.

Enum.name: BSTW_1
Enum.description: Enabled. Enables burst write of data larger than the specified port size, including 32-bit writes to 8- and 16-bit ports, 16-bit writes to 8-bit ports, and line writes to 8-, 16-, and 32-bit ports.

Enum.name: BSTR_0
Enum.description: Disabled. Data exceeding the specified port size is broken into individual, port-sized, non-burst reads. For example, a 32-bit read from an 8-bit port is broken into four 8-bit reads.

Enum.name: BSTR_1
Enum.description: Enabled. Enables data burst reads larger than the specified port size, including 32-bit reads from 8- and 16-bit ports, 16-bit reads from 8-bit ports, and line reads from 8-, 16-, and 32-bit ports.

Enum.name: BEM_0
Enum.description: FB_BE_B is asserted for data write only.

Enum.name: BEM_1
Enum.description: FB_BE_B is asserted for data read and write accesses.

Enum.name: PS_0
Enum.description: 32-bit port size. Valid data is sampled and driven on FB_D[31:0].

Enum.name: PS_1
Enum.description: 8-bit port size. Valid data is sampled and driven on FB_D[31:24] when BLS is 0b, or FB_D[7:0] when BLS is 1b.

Enum.name: PS_2
Enum.description: 16-bit port size. Valid data is sampled and driven on FB_D[31:16] when BLS is 0b, or FB_D[15:0] when BLS is 1b.

Enum.name: AA_0
Enum.description: Disabled. No internal transfer acknowledge is asserted and the cycle is terminated externally.

Enum.name: AA_1
Enum.description: Enabled. Internal transfer acknowledge is asserted as specified by WS.

Enum.name: BLS_0
Enum.description: Not shifted. Data is left-aligned on FB_AD.

Enum.name: BLS_1
Enum.description: Shifted. Data is right-aligned on FB_AD.

Enum.name: WRAH_0
Enum.description: 1 cycle (default for all but FB_CS0_B)

Enum.name: WRAH_1
Enum.description: 2 cycles

Enum.name: WRAH_2
Enum.description: 3 cycles

Enum.name: WRAH_3
Enum.description: 4 cycles (default for FB_CS0_B)

Enum.name: RDAH_0
Enum.description: When AA is 1b, 1 cycle. When AA is 0b, 0 cycles.

Enum.name: RDAH_1
Enum.description: When AA is 1b, 2 cycles. When AA is 0b, 1 cycle.

Enum.name: RDAH_2
Enum.description: When AA is 1b, 3 cycles. When AA is 0b, 2 cycles.

Enum.name: RDAH_3
Enum.description: When AA is 1b, 4 cycles. When AA is 0b, 3 cycles.

Enum.name: ASET_0
Enum.description: Assert FB_CSn_B on the first rising clock edge after the address is asserted (default for all but FB_CS0_B).

Enum.name: ASET_1
Enum.description: Assert FB_CSn_B on the second rising clock edge after the address is asserted.

Enum.name: ASET_2
Enum.description: Assert FB_CSn_B on the third rising clock edge after the address is asserted.

Enum.name: ASET_3
Enum.description: Assert FB_CSn_B on the fourth rising clock edge after the address is asserted (default for FB_CS0_B ).

Enum.name: EXTS_0
Enum.description: Disabled. FB_TS_B/FB_ALE asserts for one bus clock cycle.

Enum.name: EXTS_1
Enum.description: Enabled. FB_TS_B/FB_ALE remains asserted until the first positive clock edge after FB_CSn_B asserts.

Enum.name: SWSEN_0
Enum.description: Disabled. A number of wait states (specified by WS) are inserted before an internal transfer acknowledge is generated for all transfers.

Enum.name: SWSEN_1
Enum.description: Enabled. A number of wait states (specified by SWS) are inserted before an internal transfer acknowledge is generated for burst transfer secondary terminations.

Enum.name: GVLDM_0
Enum.description: XRDC MDACs are disabled.

Enum.name: GVLDM_1
Enum.description: XRDC MDACs are enabled.

Enum.name: VAW_0
Enum.description: Implementation is not virtualization aware.

Enum.name: VAW_1
Enum.description: Implementation is virtualization aware.

Enum.name: GVLDP_0
Enum.description: XRDC PACs/MSCs are disabled.

Enum.name: GVLDP_1
Enum.description: XRDC PACs/MSCs are enabled.

Enum.name: GVLDC_0
Enum.description: XRDC MRCs are disabled.

Enum.name: GVLDC_1
Enum.description: XRDC MRCs are enabled.

Enum.name: LK1_0
Enum.description: Register can be written by any secure privileged write.

Enum.name: LK1_1
Enum.description: Register is locked (read-only) until the next reset.

Enum.name: RSTGSM_2

Enum.description: This state encoding is never used and therefore reserved.

Enum.description: This state encoding is never used and therefore reserved.

Enum.name: FPVIOL_0
Enum.description: No protection violation detected

Enum.name: FPVIOL_1
Enum.description: Protection violation detected

Enum.name: ACCERR_0
Enum.description: No access error detected

Enum.name: ACCERR_1
Enum.description: Access error detected

Enum.name: RDCOLERR_0
Enum.description: No collision error detected

Enum.name: RDCOLERR_1
Enum.description: Collision error detected

Enum.name: CCIF_0
Enum.description: Flash command in progress

Enum.name: CCIF_1
Enum.description: Flash command has completed

Enum.name: RAMRDY_0
Enum.description: Programming acceleration RAM is not available

Enum.name: RAMRDY_1
Enum.description: Programming acceleration RAM is available

Enum.name: CRCRDY_0
Enum.description: Programming acceleration RAM is not available for CRC operations

Enum.name: CRCRDY_1
Enum.description: Programming acceleration RAM is available for CRC operations

Enum.name: SWAP_0
Enum.description: Program flash 0 block is located at relative address 0x0000

Enum.name: SWAP_1
Enum.description: Program flash 1 block is located at relative address 0x0000

Enum.name: ERSSUSP_0
Enum.description: No suspend requested

Enum.name: ERSSUSP_1
Enum.description: Suspend the current Erase Flash Sector command execution

Enum.name: ERSAREQ_0
Enum.description: No request or request complete

Enum.name: ERSAREQ_1
Enum.description: Request to: (1) run the Erase All Blocks command, (2) verify the erased state, (3) program the security byte in the Flash Configuration Field to the unsecure state, and (4) release MCU security by setting the FSEC[SEC] field to the unsecure state.

Enum.name: RDCOLLIE_0
Enum.description: Read collision error interrupt disabled

Enum.name: RDCOLLIE_1
Enum.description: Read collision error interrupt enabled. An interrupt request is generated whenever a flash read collision error is detected (see the description of FSTAT[RDCOLERR]).

Enum.name: CCIE_0
Enum.description: Command complete interrupt disabled

Enum.name: CCIE_1
Enum.description: Command complete interrupt enabled. An interrupt request is generated whenever the FSTAT[CCIF] flag is set.

Enum.name: SEC_0
Enum.description: MCU security status is secure

Enum.name: SEC_1
Enum.description: MCU security status is secure

Enum.name: SEC_2
Enum.description: MCU security status is unsecure (The standard shipping condition of the flash module is unsecure.)

Enum.name: SEC_3
Enum.description: MCU security status is secure

Enum.name: FSLACC_0
Enum.description: Factory access granted

Enum.name: FSLACC_1
Enum.description: Factory access denied

Enum.name: FSLACC_2
Enum.description: Factory access denied

Enum.name: FSLACC_3
Enum.description: Factory access granted

Enum.name: MEEN_0
Enum.description: Mass erase is enabled

Enum.name: MEEN_1
Enum.description: Mass erase is enabled

Enum.name: MEEN_2
Enum.description: Mass erase is disabled

Enum.name: MEEN_3
Enum.description: Mass erase is enabled

Enum.name: KEYEN_0
Enum.description: Backdoor key access disabled

Enum.name: KEYEN_1
Enum.description: Backdoor key access disabled (preferred KEYEN state to disable backdoor key access)

Enum.name: KEYEN_2
Enum.description: Backdoor key access enabled

Enum.name: KEYEN_3
Enum.description: Backdoor key access disabled

Enum.description: If STDBYDIS is clear, standby mode is enabled for flash block 2

Enum.name: FEATURE_0
Enum.description: Standard features implemented

Enum.name: FEATURE_4
Enum.description: Core Control and Status Registers are implemented in both MUA and MUB.

BitField.name: PARAMETER
BitField.description: This bitfield contains the parameter settings of MUA.

Enum.name: Fn_0
Enum.description: Fn bit in the MUB CR register is written 0 (default).

Enum.name: Fn_1
Enum.description: Fn bit in the MUB CR register is written 1.

Enum.name: NMIC_1
Enum.description: Writing "1" clears the NMI bit in the MUB CR register.

Enum.name: EP_0
Enum.description: The MUA side event is not pending (default).

Enum.name: EP_1
Enum.description: The MUA side event is pending.

Enum.name: HRIP_0
Enum.description: MUB didn't issue hardware reset to Processor A

Enum.name: HRIP_1
Enum.description: MUB had initiated a hardware reset to Processor A through HR bit.

Enum.name: FUP_0
Enum.description: No flags updated, initiated by the MUA, in progress (default)

Enum.name: FUP_1
Enum.description: MUA initiated flags update, processing

Enum.name: RDIP_0
Enum.description: Processor B did not exit reset

Enum.name: RDIP_1
Enum.description: Processor B exited from reset

Enum.name: RAIP_0
Enum.description: Processor B did not enter reset

Enum.name: RAIP_1
Enum.description: Processor B entered reset

Enum.name: MURIP_0
Enum.description: Processor B did not issue MU reset

Enum.name: MURIP_1
Enum.description: Processor B issued MU reset

Enum.name: RUN
Enum.description: The MUB processor is in Run Mode.

Enum.name: COO
Enum.description: The MUB processor is in COO Mode.

Enum.name: WAIT
Enum.description: The MUB processor is in WAIT Mode.

Enum.name: STOP
Enum.description: The MUB processor is in STOP/VLPS Mode.

Enum.name: DSM
Enum.description: The MUB processor is in LLS/VLLS Mode.

Enum.name: TEn_0
Enum.description: MUA TRn register is not empty.

Enum.name: TEn_1
Enum.description: MUA TRn register is empty (default).

Enum.name: RFn_0
Enum.description: MUA RRn register is not full (default).

Enum.name: RFn_1
Enum.description: MUA RRn register has received data from MUB TRn register and is ready to be read by the MUA.

Enum.name: GIPn_0
Enum.description: MUA general purpose interrupt n is not pending. (default)

Enum.name: GIPn_1
Enum.description: MUA general purpose interrupt n is pending.

Enum.name: Fn_0
Enum.description: Clears the Fn bit in the SR register.

Enum.name: Fn_1
Enum.description: Sets the Fn bit in the SR register.

Enum.name: NMI_0
Enum.description: Non-maskable interrupt is not issued to the Processor B by the Processor A (default).

Enum.name: NMI_1
Enum.description: Non-maskable interrupt is issued to the Processor B by the Processor A.

Enum.description: Registers cannot be written when locked.

Enum.name: UM_1
Enum.description: Registers can be written when locked under limited conditions.

Enum.description: RTC_WAKEUP pin asserts (active low, open drain) if the RTC interrupt asserts or the wakeup pin is turned on.

Enum.name: WPS_1

Enum.name: CPS_0
Enum.description: The prescaler output clock (as configured by TSIC) is output on RTC_CLKOUT.

Enum.name: LPOS_0

Enum.name: LPOS_1
Enum.description: RTC prescaler increments using 1 kHz LPO, bits [4:0] of the prescaler are ignored.

Enum.name: OSCE_0
Enum.description: 32.768 kHz oscillator is disabled.

Enum.name: OSCE_1

Enum.name: CLKO_0

Enum.name: CLKO_1

Enum.name: SC2P_1

Enum.description: BWT_ERR interrupt masked (default)

Enum.name: GPCNT1_IM_0
Enum.description: GPCNT1_TO interrupt enabled

Enum.name: GPCNT1_IM_1
Enum.description: GPCNT1_TO interrupt masked (default)

Enum.name: RX_DATA_IM_0
Enum.description: RX_DATA interrupt enabled

Enum.name: RX_DATA_IM_1
Enum.description: RX_DATA interrupt masked (default)

Enum.name: PEF_IM_0
Enum.description: PEF interrupt enabled

Enum.name: PEF_IM_1
Enum.description: PEF interrupt masked (default)

Enum.name: RNCK_THD_0
Enum.description: Zero Threshold. RTE will not be set

Enum.name: TNCK_THD_0
Enum.description: TNTE will never be set; retransmission after NACK reception is disabled.

Enum.name: TNCK_THD_1
Enum.description: TNTE will be set after 1 nack is received; 0 retransmissions occurs.

Enum.name: TNCK_THD_2
Enum.description: TNTE will be set after 2 nacks are received; at most 1 retransmission occurs.

Enum.name: TNCK_THD_3
Enum.description: TNTE will be set after 3 nacks are received; at most 2 retransmissions occurs.

Enum.name: TNCK_THD_15
Enum.description: TNTE will be set after 15 nacks are received; at most 14 retransmissions occurs.

Enum.name: RFO_0
Enum.description: No overrun error has occurred (default)

Enum.name: RFO_1
Enum.description: A byte was received when the received FIFO was already full

Enum.name: RX_DATA_0
Enum.description: No new byte is received

Enum.name: RX_DATA_1
Enum.description: New byte is received ans stored in Receive FIFO

Enum.name: RDTF_0
Enum.description: Number of unread bytes in receive FIFO less than the value set by RDT[3:0] (default).

Enum.name: RDTF_1
Enum.description: Number of unread bytes in receive FIFO greater or than equal to value set by RDT[3:0].

Enum.name: LRC_OK_0
Enum.description: Current LRC value does not match remainder.

Enum.name: LRC_OK_1
Enum.description: Current calculated LRC value matches the expected result (i.e. zero).

Enum.name: CRC_OK_0
Enum.description: Current CRC value does not match remainder.

Enum.name: CRC_OK_1
Enum.description: Current calculated CRC value matches the expected result.

Enum.name: CWT_ERR_0
Enum.description: No CWT violation has occurred (default).

Enum.name: CWT_ERR_1
Enum.description: Time between two consecutive characters has exceeded the value in CHAR_WAIT.

Enum.name: RTE_0
Enum.description: Number of NACKs generated by the receiver is less than the value programmed in RTH[3:0]

Enum.name: RTE_1
Enum.description: Number of NACKs generated by the receiver is equal to the value programmed in RTH[3:0]

Enum.name: BWT_ERR_0
Enum.description: Block wait time not exceeded

Enum.name: BWT_ERR_1
Enum.description: Block wait time was exceeded

Enum.name: BGT_ERR_0
Enum.description: Block guard time was sufficient

Enum.name: BGT_ERR_1
Enum.description: Block guard time was too small

Enum.name: PEF_0
Enum.description: No parity error detected

Enum.name: PEF_1
Enum.description: Parity error detected

Enum.name: FEF_0
Enum.description: No frame error detected

Enum.name: FEF_1
Enum.description: Frame error detected

Enum.name: RX_CNT_0
Enum.description: FIFO is emtpy

Enum.name: TNTE_0
Enum.description: Transmit NACK threshold has not been reached (default)

Enum.name: TNTE_1
Enum.description: Transmit NACK threshold reached; transmitter frozen

Enum.name: TFE_0
Enum.description: Transmit FIFO is not empty

Enum.name: TFE_1
Enum.description: Transmit FIFO is empty (default)

Enum.name: ETCF_0
Enum.description: Transmit pending or in progress

Enum.name: ETCF_1
Enum.description: Transmit complete (default)

Enum.name: TCF_0
Enum.description: Transmit pending or in progress

Enum.name: TCF_1
Enum.description: Transmit complete (default)

Enum.name: TFF_0
Enum.description: Transmit FIFO Full condition has not occurred (default)

Enum.name: TFF_1
Enum.description: A Transmit FIFO Full condition has occurred

Enum.name: TDTF_0
Enum.description: Number of bytes in FIFO is greater than TDT[3:0], or bit has been cleared

Enum.name: TDTF_1
Enum.description: Number of bytes in FIFO is less than or equal to TDT[3:0] (default)

Enum.name: GPCNT0_TO_0

Enum.name: GPCNT0_TO_1

Enum.name: GPCNT1_TO_0
Enum.description: GPCNT1_VAL time not reached, or bit has been cleared. (default)

Enum.name: GPCNT1_TO_1
Enum.description: General Purpose counter has reached the GPCNT1_VAL value

Enum.name: TX_CNT_0
Enum.description: FIFO is emtpy

Enum.name: SAPD_0

Enum.name: SVCC_EN_0

Enum.description: Smart Card Voltage enabled

Enum.description: VCC_EN is active low. Polarity of SVCC_EN is inverted.

Enum.name: SRST_0

Enum.name: SRST_1
Enum.description: Smart Card Reset is de-asserted

Enum.name: SCEN_0
Enum.description: Smart Card Clock Disabled

Enum.name: SCEN_1
Enum.description: Smart Card Clock Enabled

Enum.name: SCSP_0

Enum.name: SCSP_1
Enum.description: Clock is logic 1 when stopped by SCEN

Enum.name: SPD_0

Enum.description: MSB (bit9, bit8, bit7 or bit6) is the first bit that is transmitted following the start bit depending on the setting of CTRL[M], CTRL[PE] and BAUD[M10]. Further, the first bit received after the start bit is identified as bit9, bit8, bit7 or bit6 depending on the setting of CTRL[M] and CTRL[PE].

Enum.name: TXCTSE_0
Enum.description: CTS has no effect on the transmitter.

Enum.name: TXCTSE_1
Enum.description: Enables clear-to-send operation. The transmitter checks the state of CTS each time it is ready to send a character. If CTS is asserted, the character is sent. If CTS is deasserted, the signal TXD remains in the mark state and transmission is delayed until CTS is asserted. Changes in CTS as a character is being sent do not affect its transmission.

Enum.name: TXRTSE_0
Enum.description: The transmitter has no effect on RTS.

Enum.name: TXRTSE_1
Enum.description: When a character is placed into an empty transmitter data buffer , RTS asserts one bit time before the start bit is transmitted. RTS deasserts one bit time after all characters in the transmitter data buffer and shift register are completely sent, including the last stop bit.

Enum.name: TXRTSPOL_0
Enum.description: Transmitter RTS is active low.

Enum.name: TXRTSPOL_1
Enum.description: Transmitter RTS is active high.

Enum.name: RXRTSE_0
Enum.description: The receiver has no effect on RTS.

Enum.name: RXRTSE_1
Enum.description: RTS is deasserted if the receiver data register is full or a start bit has been detected that would cause the receiver data register to become full. RTS is asserted if the receiver data register is not full and has not detected a start bit that would cause the receiver data register to become full.

Enum.description: CTS input is sampled when the transmitter is idle.

Enum.name: TXCTSE_0
Enum.description: CTS has no effect on the transmitter.

Enum.name: TXCTSE_1
Enum.description: Enables clear-to-send operation. The transmitter checks the state of CTS each time it is ready to send a character. If CTS is asserted, the character is sent. If CTS is deasserted, the signal TXD remains in the mark state and transmission is delayed until CTS is asserted. Changes in CTS as a character is being sent do not affect its transmission.

Enum.name: TXRTSE_0
Enum.description: The transmitter has no effect on RTS.

Enum.name: TXRTSE_1
Enum.description: When a character is placed into an empty transmitter data buffer , RTS asserts one bit time before the start bit is transmitted. RTS deasserts one bit time after all characters in the transmitter data buffer and shift register are completely sent, including the last stop bit.

Enum.name: TXRTSPOL_0
Enum.description: Transmitter RTS is active low.

Enum.name: TXRTSPOL_1
Enum.description: Transmitter RTS is active high.

Enum.name: RXRTSE_0
Enum.description: The receiver has no effect on RTS.

Enum.name: RXRTSE_1
Enum.description: RTS is deasserted if the receiver data register is full or a start bit has been detected that would cause the receiver data register to become full. RTS is asserted if the receiver data register is not full and has not detected a start bit that would cause the receiver data register to become full.

Enum.name: TXCTSC_0
Enum.description: CTS input is sampled at the start of each character.

Enum.name: TXCTSC_1
Enum.description: CTS input is sampled when the transmitter is idle.

Enum.name: TXCTSSRC_0
Enum.description: CTS input is the CTS_B pin.

Enum.name: TXCTSSRC_1
Enum.description: CTS input is the inverted Receiver Match result.

Enum.description: MSB (bit9, bit8, bit7 or bit6) is the first bit that is transmitted following the start bit depending on the setting of CTRL[M], CTRL[PE] and BAUD[M10]. Enum.name: ISF_1
Enum.description: Configured interrupt is detected. If the pin is configured to generate a DMA request, then the corresponding flag will be cleared automatically at the completion of the requested DMA transfer. Otherwise, the flag remains set until a logic 1 is written to the flag. If the pin is configured for a level sensitive interrupt and the pin remains asserted, then the flag is set again immediately after it is cleared.

Enum.name: IRQC_13
Enum.description: Enable active high trigger output, flag is disabled. [The trigger output goes to the trigger mux, which allows pins to trigger other peripherals (configurable polarity; 1 pin per port; if multiple pins are configured, then they are ORed together to create the trigger)]

Enum.name: IRQC_14
Enum.description: Enable active low trigger output, flag is disabled.

Enum.name: ISF_0
Enum.description: Configured interrupt is not detected.

Enum.name: ISF_1
Enum.description: Configured interrupt is detected. If the pin is configured to generate a DMA request, then the corresponding flag will be cleared automatically at the completion of the requested DMA transfer. Otherwise, the flag remains set until a logic 1 is written to the flag. If the pin is configured for a level sensitive interrupt and the pin remains asserted, then the flag is set again immediately after it is cleared.

BitField.description: For bit STIMENA[n], in register ITM_TERx: 0 = Stimulus port (32x + n) disabled 1 = Stimulus port (32x + n) enabled

BitField.name: PRIVMASK
BitField.description: Bit mask to enable tracing on ITM stimulus ports: Bit [0] = stimulus port [7:0] Bit [1] = stimulus port [15:8] Bit [2] = stimulus port [23:16] Bit [3] = stimulus port [31:24]

Enum.name: SWOENA_0
Enum.description: Timestamp counter uses the processor system clock.

Enum.name: SWOENA_1
Enum.description: Timestamp counter uses asynchronous clock from the TPIU interface.

BitField.name: TSPrescale
BitField.description: Local timestamp prescaler, used with the trace packet reference clock.

Enum.name: TSPrescale_0
Enum.description: No prescaling.

Enum.name: TSPrescale_1
Enum.description: Divide by 4.

Enum.name: TSPrescale_2
Enum.description: Divide by 16.

Enum.name: TSPrescale_3
Enum.description: Divide by 64.

BitField.name: GTSFREQ
BitField.description: Global timestamp frequency. Defines how often the ITM generates a global timestamp, based on the global timestamp clock frequency, or disables generation of global timestamps.

Enum.name: GTSFREQ_0
Enum.description: Disable generation of global timestamps.

Enum.name: GTSFREQ_1
Enum.description: Generate timestamp request whenever the ITM detects a change in global timestamp counter bits [47:7]. This is approximately every 128 cycles.

Enum.name: GTSFREQ_2
Enum.description: Generate timestamp request whenever the ITM detects a change in global timestamp counter bits [47:13]. This is approximately every 8192 cycles.

Enum.name: GTSFREQ_3
Enum.description: Generate a timestamp after every packet, if the output FIFO is empty.

BitField.name: TraceBusID
BitField.description: Identifier for multi-source trace stream formatting. If multi-source trace is in use, the debugger must write a non-zero value to this field.

BitField.name: BUSY
BitField.description: Indicates whether the ITM is currently processing events: 0: ITM is not processing any events. 1: ITM events present and being drained.

Enum.name: BUSY_0
Enum.description: ITM is not processing any events.

Enum.name: BUSY_1
Enum.description: ITM events present and beeing drained.

BitField.name: WriteAccessCode
BitField.description: Write Access Code. A write of 0xC5ACCE55 enables further write access to this device. An invalid write will have the affect of removing write access.

BitField.name: IMP
BitField.description: Lock mechanism is implemented. This bit always reads 1.

BitField.name: STATUS
BitField.description: Lock Status. This bit is HIGH when the device is locked, and LOW when unlocked.

BitField.name: s8BIT
BitField.description: Access Lock Register size. This bit reads 0 to indicate a 32-bit register is present.

RegisterGroup.name: DWT
RegisterGroup.description: Data Watchpoint and Trace Unit Registers

BitField.name: CYCCNTENA
BitField.description: CYCCNTENA bit. Enables CYCCNT. This bit is UNK/SBZP if the NOCYCCNT bit is RAO.

BitField.name: POSTPRESET
BitField.description: POSTPRESET bits. Reload value for the POSTCNT counter. This field is UNK/SBZP if the NOCYCCNT bit is RAO.

BitField.name: POSTINIT
BitField.description: POSTINIT bits. Initial value for the POSTCNT counter. This field is UNK/SBZP if the NOCYCCNT bit is RAO.

BitField.name: CYCTAP
BitField.description: CYCTAP bit. Selects the position of the POSTCNT tap on the CYCCNT counter. This bit is UNK/SBZP if the NOCYCCNT bit is RAO.

Enum.name: CYCTAP_0
Enum.description: POSTCNT tap at CYCCNT[6].

Enum.name: CYCTAP_1
Enum.description: POSTCNT tap at CYCCNT[10].

BitField.name: SYNCTAP
BitField.description: SYNCTAP bits. Selects the position of the synchronization packet counter tap on the CYCCNT counter. This determines the Synchronization packet rate.

Enum.name: SYNCTAP_0
Enum.description: Disabled. No Synchronization packets.

Enum.name: SYNCTAP_1
Enum.description: Synchronization counter tap at CYCCNT[24].

Enum.name: SYNCTAP_2
Enum.description: Synchronization counter tap at CYCCNT[26].

Enum.name: SYNCTAP_3
Enum.description: Synchronization counter tap at CYCCNT[28].

BitField.name: PCSAMPLENA
BitField.description: PCSAMPLENA bit. Enables use of POSTCNT counter as a timer for Periodic PC sample packet generation. This bit is UNK/SBZP if the NOTRCPKT bit is RAO or the NOCYCCNT bit is RAO.

Enum.name: PCSAMPLENA_0
Enum.description: No Periodic PC sample packets generated.

Enum.name: PCSAMPLENA_1
Enum.description: Periodic PC sample packets generated.

BitField.name: EXCTRCENA
BitField.description: EXCTRCENA bit. Enables generation of exception trace. This bit is UNK/SBZP if the NOTRCPKT bit is RAO.

BitField.name: CPIEVTENA
BitField.description: CPIEVTENA bit. Enables generation of the CPI counter overflow event. This bit is UNK/SBZP if the NOPRFCNT bit is RAO.

BitField.name: EXCEVTENA
BitField.description: EXCEVTENA bit. Enables generation of the Exception overhead counter overflow event. This bit is UNK/SBZP if the NOPRFCNT bit is RAO.

BitField.name: SLEEPEVTENA
BitField.description: SLEEPEVTENA bit. Enables generation of the Sleep counter overflow event. This bit is UNK/SBZP if the NOPRFCNT bit is RAO.

BitField.name: LSUEVTENA
BitField.description: LSUEVTENA bit. Enables generation of the LSU counter overflow event. This bit is UNK/SBZP if the NOPRFCNT bit is RAO.

BitField.name: FOLDEVTENA
BitField.description: FOLDEVTENA bit. Enables generation of the Folded-instruction counter overflow event. This bit is UNK/SBZP if the NOPRFCNT bit is RAO.

BitField.name: CYCEVTENA
BitField.description: CYCEVTENA bit. Enables POSTCNT underflow Event counter packets generation. This bit is UNK/SBZP if the NOTRCPKT bit is RAO or the NOCYCCNT bit is RAO.

Enum.name: CYCEVTENA_0
Enum.description: No POSTCNT underflow packets generated.

Enum.name: CYCEVTENA_1
Enum.description: POSTCNT underflow packets generated, if PCSAMPLENA set to 0.

BitField.name: NOPFRCNT
BitField.description: NOPFRCNT bit. Shows whether the implementation supports the profiling counters.

Enum.name: NOPFRCNT_1
Enum.description: Not supported.

BitField.name: NOCYCCNT
BitField.description: NOCYCCNT bit. Shows whether the implementation supports a cycle counter.

Enum.name: NOCYCCNT_0
Enum.description: Cycle counter supported.

Enum.name: NOCYCCNT_1
Enum.description: Cycle counter not supported.

BitField.name: NOEXTTRIG
BitField.description: NOEXTRRIG bit. Shows whether the implementation includes external match signals, CMPMATCH[N].

Enum.name: NOEXTTRIG_0
Enum.description: CMPMATCH[N] supported.

Enum.name: NOEXTTRIG_1
Enum.description: CMPMATCH[N] not supported.

BitField.name: NOTRCPKT
BitField.description: NOTRCPKT bit. Shows whether the implementation supports trace sampling and exception tracing. If this bit is RAZ, the NOCYCCNT bit must also RAZ.

Enum.name: NOTRCPKT_0
Enum.description: Trace sampling and exception tracing supported.

Enum.name: NOTRCPKT_1
Enum.description: Trace sampling and exception tracing not supported.

BitField.name: NUMCOMP
BitField.description: NUMCOMP bits. Number of comparators implemented. A value of zero indicates no comparator support.

BitField.name: CYCCNT
BitField.description: CYCCNT[31:0]. Incrementing cycle counter value. When enabled, CYCCNT increments on each processor clock cycle. On overflow, CYCCNT wraps to zero.

BitField.name: CPICNT
BitField.description: CPICNT[7:0]. The base CPI counter. Counts additional cycles required to execute multi-cycle instructions, except those recorded by DWT_LSUCNT, and counts any instruction fetch stalls.

BitField.name: EXCCNT
BitField.description: EXCCNT[7:0]. The exception overhead counter. Counts the total cycles spent in exception processing.

BitField.name: SLEEPCNT
BitField.description: SLEEPCNT[7:0]. Sleep counter. Counts the total number of cycles that the processor is sleeping.

BitField.name: LSUCNT
BitField.description: LSUCNT[7:0]. Load-store counter. Increments on any additional cycles required to execute load or store instructions.

BitField.name: FOLDCNT
BitField.description: FOLDCNT[7:0]. Folded-instruction counter. Increments on each instruction that takes 0 cycles.

BitField.name: EIASAMPLE
BitField.description: EIASAMPLE[31:0]. Executed Instruction Address sample value.

BitField.name: MASK
BitField.description: MASK[4:0]. The size of the ignore mask, 0-31 bits, applied to address range matching. The maximum mask size is IMPLEMENTATION DEFINED. A debugger can write 0b11111 to this field and then read the register back to determine the maximum mask size supported.

BitField.name: FUNCTION
BitField.description: FUNCTION[3:0]. Selects action taken on comparator match. This field resets to zero.

BitField.name: EMITRANGE
BitField.description: EMITRANGE bit. If the implementation supports trace sampling, enables generation of Data trace address offset packets, that hold Daddr[15:0]. If DWT_CTRL.NOTRCPKT is RAZ then this bit is UNK/SBZP.

Enum.name: EMITRANGE_0
Enum.description: Data trace address offset packets disabled.

Enum.name: EMITRANGE_1
Enum.description: Enable Data trace address offset packet generation.

BitField.name: CYCMATCH
BitField.description: CYCMATCH bit. If the implementation supports cycle counting, enable cycle count comparison for comparator 0. If DWT_CTRL.NOCYCCNT is RAZ then this bit is UNK/SBZP.

Enum.name: CYCMATCH_0
Enum.description: No comparison is performed.

Enum.name: CYCMATCH_1
Enum.description: Compare DWT_COMP0 with the cycle counter, DWT_CYCCNT.

BitField.name: DATAVMATCH
BitField.description: DATAVMATCH bit. Enables data value comparison, if supported. For comparator 0, when the CYCMATCH is set to 1, DATAVMATCH must be set to 0 for it to perform cycle count comparison. See LNK1ENA, DATAVSIZE, DATAVADDR0 and DATAVADDR1 for related information. If the implementation does not support data value comparison this bit is RAZ/WI.

Enum.name: DATAVMATCH_0
Enum.description: Perform address comparison.

Enum.name: DATAVMATCH_1
Enum.description: Perform data value comparison.

BitField.name: LNK1ENA
BitField.description: LNK1ENA bit. Indicates whether the implementation supports use of a second linked comparator. When LNK1ENA is RAO, the DATAVADDR1 field specifies the comparator to use as the second linked comparator.

Enum.name: LNK1ENA_0
Enum.description: Second linked comparator not supported.

Enum.name: LNK1ENA_1
Enum.description: Second linked comparator supported.

BitField.name: DATAVSIZE
BitField.description: DATAVSIZE[1:0]. For data value matching, specifies the size of the required data comparison.

BitField.name: DATAVADDR0
BitField.description: DATAVADDR0[3:0]. When the DATAVMATCH bit is set to 1 this field can hold the comparator number of a comparator to use for linked address comparison. The DWT unit ignores the value of this field if the DATAVMATCH bit is set to 0.

BitField.name: DATAVADDR1
BitField.description: DATAVADDR1[3:0]. When the DATAVMATCH and LNK1ENA bits are both 1, this field can hold the comparator number of a second comparator to use for linked address comparison. The DWT unit ignores the value of this field unless the LNK1ENA bit is RAO and the DATAVMATCH bit is set to 1. If LNK1ENA is RAZ, this field is RAZ/WI.

BitField.name: MATCHED
BitField.description: MATCHED bit. Comparator match. A value of 1 indicates that the operation defined by the FUNCTION field occurred since the last read of the register. Reading the register clears this bit to 0.

Enum.name: MATCHED_0
Enum.description: No match.

Enum.name: ENABLE_0
Enum.description: FPB disabled.

Enum.name: ENABLE_1
Enum.description: FPB enabled.

BitField.name: KEY
BitField.description: KEY bit. On any write to FP_CTRL, the FPB unit ignores the write unless this bit is 1. This bit is RAZ.

BitField.name: NUM_CODE_least
BitField.description: NUM_CODE[3:0]. The least significant bits of NUM_CODE, the number of instruction address comparators. If NUM_CODE[6:0] is zero, the implementation does not support any instruction address comparators.

BitField.name: NUM_LIT
BitField.description: NUM_LIT bits. The number of literal address comparators supported. If this field is zero, the implementation does not support literal comparators.

BitField.name: NUM_CODE_most

Register.name: DHCSR_Read
Register.description: Debug Halting Control and Status Register

BitField.name: C_DEBUGEN
BitField.description: Halting debug enable bit. If a debugger writes to DHCSR to change the value of this bit from 0 to 1, it must also write 0 to the C_MASKINTS bit, otherwise behavior is UNPREDICTABLE. This bit can only be set to 1 from the DAP, it cannot be set to 1 under software control. This bit is 0 after a Power-on reset.

BitField.name: C_HALT
BitField.description: Processor halt bit. This bit is UNKNOWN after a Power-on reset.

Enum.name: C_HALT_0
Enum.description: No effect.

Enum.name: C_HALT_1
Enum.description: Halt the processor.

BitField.name: C_STEP
BitField.description: Processor step bit. This bit is UNKNOWN after a Power-on reset.

Enum.name: C_STEP_0
Enum.description: No effect.

Enum.name: C_STEP_1
Enum.description: Step the processor.

BitField.name: C_MASKINTS
BitField.description: C_MASKINTS bit. When debug is enabled, the debugger can write to this bit to mask PendSV, SysTick and external configurable interrupts. The effect of any attempt to change the value of this bit is UNPREDICTABLE unless both: - before the write to DHCSR, the value of the C_HALT bit is 1. - the write to the DHCSR that changes the C_MASKINTS bit also writes 1 to the C_HALT bit. This means that a single write to DHCSR cannot set the C_HALT to 0 and change the value of the C_MASKINTS bit. The bit does not affect NMI. When DHCSR.C_DEBUGEN is set to 0, the value of this bit is UNKNOWN. This bit is UNKNOWN after a Power-on reset.

Enum.name: C_MASKINTS_0
Enum.description: Do not mask.

Enum.name: C_MASKINTS_1
Enum.description: Mask PenSV, SysTick and external configurable interrupts.

BitField.name: C_SNAPSTALL
BitField.description: C_SNAPSTALL bit. If the processor is stalled on a load or store operation, a debugger can set this bit to 1 to attempt to break the stall. The effect of setting this bit to 1 is UNPREDICTABLE unless the DHCSR write also sets C_DEBUGEN and C_HALT to 1. This means that if the processor is not already in Debug statea it enters Debug state when the stalled instruction completes. Writing 1 to this bit makes the state of the memory system UNPREDICTABLE. Therefore, if a debugger writes 1 to this bit it must reset the processor before leaving Debug state. A Power-on reset sets this bit to 0.

Enum.name: C_SNAPSTALL_0
Enum.description: No action.

Enum.name: C_SNAPSTALL_1
Enum.description: Attempt to force any stalled load or store instruction to complete.

BitField.name: S_REGRDY
BitField.description: S_REGRDY bit. A handshake flag for transfers through the DCRDR: - Writing to DCRSR clears the bit to 0. - Completion of the DCRDR transfer then sets the bit to 1. This bit is valid only when the processor is in Debug state, otherwise the bit is UNKNOWN.

Enum.name: S_REGRDY_0
Enum.description: There has been a write to the DCRDR, but the transfer is not complete.

Enum.name: S_REGRDY_1
Enum.description: The transfer to or from the DCRDR is complete.

BitField.name: S_HALT
BitField.description: S_HALT bit. Indicates whether the processor is in Debug state.

Enum.name: S_HALT_0
Enum.description: Not in Debug state.

Enum.name: S_HALT_1
Enum.description: In Debug state.

BitField.name: S_SLEEP
BitField.description: S_SLEEP bit. Indicates whether the processor is sleeping. The debugger must set the C_HALT bit to 1 to gain control, or wait for an interrupt or other wakeup event to wakeup the system.

Enum.name: S_SLEEP_0
Enum.description: Not sleeping.

BitField.name: S_LOCKUP
BitField.description: S_LOCKUP bit. Indicates whether the processor is locked up because of an unrecoverable exception. This bit can only be read as 1 by a remote debugger, using the DAP. The value of 1 indicates that the processor is running but locked up. The bit clears to 0 when the processor enters Debug state.

Enum.name: S_LOCKUP_0
Enum.description: Not locked up

Enum.name: S_LOCKUP_1
Enum.description: Locked up

BitField.name: S_RETIRE_ST
BitField.description: S_RETIRE_ST bit. Indicates whether the processor has completed the execution of an instruction since the last read of DHCSR. This is a sticky bit, that clears to 0 on a read of DHCSR. A debugger can check this bit to determine if the processor is stalled on a load, store or fetch access. This bit is UNKNOWN after a Power-on or Local reset, but then is set to 1 as soon as the processor executes and retires an instruction.

Enum.name: S_RETIRE_ST_0
Enum.description: No instruction retired since last DHCSR read.

Enum.name: S_RETIRE_ST_1
Enum.description: At least one instruction retired since last DHCSR read.

BitField.name: S_RESET_ST
BitField.description: S_RESET_ST bit. Indicates whether the processor has been reset since the last read of DHCSR. This is a sticky bit, that clears to 0 on a read of DHCSR.

Enum.name: S_RESET_ST_0
Enum.description: No reset since last DHCSR read.

Enum.name: S_RESET_ST_1
Enum.description: At least one reset since last DHCSR read.

Register.name: DHCSR_Write
Register.description: Debug Halting Control and Status Register

BitField.name: C_DEBUGEN
BitField.description: Halting debug enable bit. If a debugger writes to DHCSR to change the value of this bit from 0 to 1, it must also write 0 to the C_MASKINTS bit, otherwise behavior is UNPREDICTABLE. This bit can only be set to 1 from the DAP, it cannot be set to 1 under software control. This bit is 0 after a Power-on reset.

BitField.name: C_HALT
BitField.description: Processor halt bit. This bit is UNKNOWN after a Power-on reset.

Enum.name: C_HALT_0
Enum.description: No effect.

Enum.name: C_HALT_1
Enum.description: Halt the processor.

BitField.name: C_STEP
BitField.description: Processor step bit. This bit is UNKNOWN after a Power-on reset.

Enum.name: C_STEP_0
Enum.description: No effect.

Enum.name: C_STEP_1
Enum.description: Step the processor.

BitField.name: C_MASKINTS
BitField.description: C_MASKINTS bit. When debug is enabled, the debugger can write to this bit to mask PendSV, SysTick and external configurable interrupts. The effect of any attempt to change the value of this bit is UNPREDICTABLE unless both: - before the write to DHCSR, the value of the C_HALT bit is 1. - the write to the DHCSR that changes the C_MASKINTS bit also writes 1 to the C_HALT bit. This means that a single write to DHCSR cannot set the C_HALT to 0 and change the value of the C_MASKINTS bit. The bit does not affect NMI. When DHCSR.C_DEBUGEN is set to 0, the value of this bit is UNKNOWN. This bit is UNKNOWN after a Power-on reset.

Enum.name: C_MASKINTS_0
Enum.description: Do not mask.

Enum.name: C_MASKINTS_1
Enum.description: Mask PenSV, SysTick and external configurable interrupts.

BitField.name: C_SNAPSTALL
BitField.description: C_SNAPSTALL bit. If the processor is stalled on a load or store operation, a debugger can set this bit to 1 to attempt to break the stall. The effect of setting this bit to 1 is UNPREDICTABLE unless the DHCSR write also sets C_DEBUGEN and C_HALT to 1. This means that if the processor is not already in Debug statea it enters Debug state when the stalled instruction completes. Writing 1 to this bit makes the state of the memory system UNPREDICTABLE. Therefore, if a debugger writes 1 to this bit it must reset the processor before leaving Debug state. A Power-on reset sets this bit to 0.

Enum.name: C_SNAPSTALL_0
Enum.description: No action.

Enum.name: C_SNAPSTALL_1
Enum.description: Attempt to force any stalled load or store instruction to complete.

BitField.name: DBGKEY
BitField.description: Debug key: Software must write 0xA05F to this field to enable write accesses to bits [15:0], otherwise the processor ignores the write access.

BitField.name: REGSEL
BitField.description: REGSEL bits. Specifies the ARM core register, special-purpose register, or Floating-point extension register, to transfer.

BitField.name: REGWnR
BitField.description: REGWnR bit. Specifies the access type for the transfer.

BitField.name: DBGTMP
BitField.description: DBGTMP bits. Data temporary cache, for reading and writing the ARM core registers, special-purpose registers, and Floating-point extension registers. The value of this register is UNKNOWN: - on reset - if the processor is in Debug state, the debugger has written to DCRSR since entering Debug state and DHCSR.S_REGRDY is set to 0.

Register.name: DEMCR
Register.description: Debug Exception and Monitor Control Register

BitField.name: VC_CORERESET
BitField.description: VC_CORERESET bit. Enable Reset Vector Catch. This causes a Local reset to halt a running system. If DHCSR.C_DEBUGEN is set to 0, the processor ignores the value of this bit.

Enum.name: VC_CORERESET_0
Enum.description: Reset Vector Catch disabled.

Enum.name: VC_CORERESET_1
Enum.description: Reset Vector Catch enabled.

BitField.name: VC_MMERR
BitField.description: VC_MMERR bit. Enable halting debug trap on a MemManage exception. If DHCSR.C_DEBUGEN is set to 0, the processor ignores the value of this bit.

Enum.name: VC_MMERR_0
Enum.description: Halting debug trap disabled.

Enum.name: VC_MMERR_1
Enum.description: Halting debug trap enabled.

BitField.name: VC_NOCPERR
BitField.description: VC_NOCPERR bit. Enable halting debug trap on a UsageFault caused by an access to a Coprocessor. If DHCSR.C_DEBUGEN is set to 0, the processor ignores the value of this bit.

Enum.name: VC_NOCPERR_0
Enum.description: Halting debug trap disabled.

Enum.name: VC_NOCPERR_1
Enum.description: Halting debug trap enabled.

BitField.name: VC_CHKERR
BitField.description: VC_CHKERR bit. Enable halting debug trap on a UsageFault exception caused by a checking error, for example an alignment check error. If DHCSR.C_DEBUGEN is set to 0, the processor ignores the value of this bit.

Enum.name: VC_CHKERR_0
Enum.description: Halting debug trap disabled.

Enum.name: VC_CHKERR_1
Enum.description: Halting debug trap enabled.

BitField.name: VC_STATERR
BitField.description: VC_STATERR bit. Enable halting debug trap on a UsageFault exception caused by a state information error, for example an Undefined Instruction exception. If DHCSR.C_DEBUGEN is set to 0, the processor ignores the value of this bit.

Enum.name: VC_STATERR_0
Enum.description: Halting debug trap disabled.

Enum.name: VC_STATERR_1
Enum.description: Halting debug trap enabled.

BitField.name: VC_BUSERR
BitField.description: VC_BUSERR bit. Enable halting debug trap on a BusFault exception. If DHCSR.C_DEBUGEN is set to 0, the processor ignores the value of this bit.

Enum.name: VC_BUSERR_0
Enum.description: Halting debug trap disabled.

Enum.name: VC_BUSERR_1
Enum.description: Halting debug trap enabled.

BitField.name: VC_INTERR
BitField.description: VC_INTERR bit. Enable halting debug trap on a fault occurring during exception entry or exception return. If DHCSR.C_DEBUGEN is set to 0, the processor ignores the value of this bit.

Enum.name: VC_INTERR_0
Enum.description: Halting debug trap disabled.

Enum.name: VC_INTERR_1
Enum.description: Halting debug trap enabled.

BitField.name: VC_HARDERR
BitField.description: VC_HARDERR bit. Enable halting debug trap on a HardFault exception. If DHCSR.C_DEBUGEN is set to 0, the processor ignores the value of this bit.

Enum.name: VC_HARDERR_0
Enum.description: Halting debug trap disabled.

Enum.name: VC_HARDERR_1
Enum.description: Halting debug trap enabled.

BitField.name: MON_EN
BitField.description: MON_EN bit. Enable the DebugMonitor exception. If DHCSR.C_DEBUGEN is set to 1, the processor ignores the value of this bit.

Enum.name: MON_EN_0
Enum.description: DebugMonitor exception disabled.

Enum.name: MON_EN_1
Enum.description: DebugMonitor exception enabled.

BitField.name: MON_PEND
BitField.description: MON_PEND bit. Sets or clears the pending state of the DebugMonitor exception. When the DebugMonitor exception is pending it becomes active subject to the exception priority rules. A debugger can use this bit to wakeup the monitor using the DAP. The effect of setting this bit to 1 is not affected by the value of the MON_EN bit. A debugger can set MON_PEND to 1, and force the processor to take a DebugMonitor exception, even when MON_EN is set to 0.

Enum.name: MON_PEND_0
Enum.description: Clear the status of the DebugMonitor exception to not pending.

Enum.name: MON_PEND_1
Enum.description: Set the status of the DebugMonitor exception to pending.

BitField.name: MON_STEP
BitField.description: MON_STEP bit. When MON_EN is set to 0, this feature is disabled and the processor ignores MON_STEP. When MON_EN is set to 1, the meaning of MON_STEP is: 0 = Do not step the processor. 1 = Step the processor. Setting this bit to 1 makes the step request pending. The request becomes active when the processor returns from the DebugMonitor handler to the code being debugged. The effect of setting this bit to 1 is UNPREDICTABLE if the code being debugged is executing at an execution priority that is lower than the priority of the DebugMonitor exception. This is the debug monitor equivalent of DHCSR.C_STEP in Debug state.

Enum.name: MON_STEP_0
Enum.description: Do not step the processor.

Enum.name: MON_STEP_1
Enum.description: Step the processor.

BitField.name: MON_REQ
BitField.description: DebugMonitor semaphore bit. The processor does not use this bit. The monitor software defines the meaning and use of this bit.

BitField.name: TRCENA
BitField.description: TRCENA bit. Global enable for all DWT and ITM features. If the DWT and ITM blocks are not implemented, this bit is UNK/SBZP. When TRCENA is set to 0: - DWT registers return UNKNOWN values on reads. Whether the processor ignores writes to the DWT unit is IMPLEMENTATION DEFINED. - ITM registers return UNKNOWN values on reads. Whether the processor ignores writes to the ITM unit is IMPLEMENTATION DEFINED. Setting this bit to 0 might not stop all events. To ensure all events are stopped, software must set all DWT and ITM feature enable bits to 0, and then set this bit to 0. The effect of this bit on the TPIU, ETM, and other system trace components is IMPLEMENTATION DEFINED.

Enum.name: TRCENA_0
Enum.description: DWT and ITM blocks disabled.

Enum.name: TRCENA_1
Enum.description: DWT and ITM blocks enabled.

BitField.name: SWIDTH
BitField.description: SWIDTH[N] represents a trace port width of (N+1). The meaning of each bit is: 0 = Width (N+1) not supported. 1 = Width (N+1) supported.

BitField.name: CWIDTH
BitField.description: CWIDTH[N] represents a trace port width of (N+1). The meaning of each bit is: 0 = Width (N+1) is not the current trace port width. 1 = Width (N+1) is the current trace port width.

BitField.name: TXMODE
BitField.description: Specified the protocol for trace output from the TPIU.

Enum.name: TXMODE_0
Enum.description: Parallel trace port mode.

Enum.name: TXMODE_1
Enum.description: Asynchronous SWO, using Manchester encoding.

Enum.name: TXMODE_2
Enum.description: Asynchronous SWO, using NRZ encoding.

BitField.name: F1InProg
BitField.description: F1InProg. This bit always reads zero

BitField.name: FtStopped
BitField.description: FtStopped. This bit always reads zero

BitField.name: TCPresent
BitField.description: TCPresent. This bit always reads zero

Enum.name: EnFCont_0
Enum.description: Continuous formatting disabled.

Enum.name: EnFCont_1
Enum.description: Continuous formatting enabled.

BitField.name: TrigIn
BitField.description: This bit Reads-As-One (RAO), specifying that triggers are inserted when a trigger pin is asserted.

BitField.name: CycCount
BitField.description: CycCount[11:0]. 12-bit counter value to indicate the number of complete frames between full synchronization packets. Default value is 64 (0x40).

BitField.name: TRIGGER
BitField.description: TRIGGER input value. When read, this bit returns the TRIGGER input.

BitField.name: ETMdata0
BitField.description: ETM trace data. The TPIU discards this data when the registers is read.

BitField.name: ETMdata1
BitField.description: ETM trace data. The TPIU discards this data when the registers is read.

BitField.name: ETMdata2
BitField.description: ETM trace data. The TPIU discards this data when the registers is read.

BitField.name: ETMbytecount
BitField.description: Number of bytes of ETM trace data since last read of Integration ETM Data Register.

BitField.name: ETMATVALID
BitField.description: Returns the value of the ETM ATVALID signal.

BitField.name: ITMbytecount
BitField.description: Number of bytes of ITM trace data since last read of Integration ITM Data Register.

BitField.name: ITMATVALID
BitField.description: Returns the value of the ITM ATVALID signal.

BitField.name: ATREADY1_ATREADY2
BitField.description: This bit sets the value of both the ETM and ITM ATREADY.

BitField.name: ATVALID1_ATVALID2
BitField.description: A read of this bit returns the value of ATVALIDS1 OR-ed with ATVALIDS2.

BitField.name: ITMdata0
BitField.description: ITM trace data. The TPIU discards this data when the registers is read.

BitField.name: ITMdata1
BitField.description: ITM trace data. The TPIU discards this data when the registers is read.

BitField.name: ITMdata2
BitField.description: ITM trace data. The TPIU discards this data when the registers is read.

BitField.name: ETMbytecount
BitField.description: Number of bytes of ETM trace data since last read of Integration ETM Data Register.

BitField.name: ETMATVALID
BitField.description: Returns the value of the ETM ATVALID signal.

BitField.name: ITMbytecount
BitField.description: Number of bytes of ITM trace data since last read of Integration ITM Data Register.

BitField.name: ITMATVALID
BitField.description: Returns the value of the ITM ATVALID signal.

BitField.name: Mode
BitField.description: Specifies the current mode for the TPIU.

Enum.name: Mode_0
Enum.description: normal mode

Enum.name: Mode_1
Enum.description: integration test mode

Enum.name: Mode_2
Enum.description: integration data test mode

BitField.name: CLAIMSET
BitField.description: A bit programmable register bank which sets the Claim Tag Value. Write 1 to set the bit in the claim tag. A read will return a logic 1 for all implemented locations.

BitField.name: CLAIMCLR
BitField.description: A bit programmable register bank that is zero at reset. Write 1 to clear the bit in the claim tag. On reads, returns the current setting of the claim tag.

BitField.name: NumberOfTraceInputs
BitField.description: Number of trace inputs. Specifies the number of trace inputs: b000000 = 1 input b000001 = 2 inputs If your implementation includes an ETM, the value of this field is b000001.

BitField.name: TRACECELKIN
BitField.description: Asynchronous TRACECLKIN. Specifies whether TRACECLKIN can be asynchronous to CLK.

Enum.name: TRACECELKIN_0
Enum.description: b0 = TRACECLKIN must be synchronous to CLK

Enum.name: TRACECELKIN_1
Enum.description: b1 = TRACECLKIN can be asynchronous to CLK

BitField.name: MinimumBufferSize
BitField.description: Minimum buffer size. Specifies the minimum TPIU buffer size: b010 = 4 bytes

BitField.name: TraceAndClockModes
BitField.description: Trace and clock modes. This bit Reads-As-Zero (RAZ), indicating that tracedata and clock modes are supported.

Enum.name: TraceAndClockModes_1
Enum.description: Not supported

BitField.name: Manchester
BitField.description: Asynchronous Serial Wire Output (Manchester). This bit Reads-As-One (RAO), indicating that the output is supported.

BitField.name: NRZ
BitField.description: Asynchronous Serial Wire Output (NRZ). This bit Reads-As-One (RAO), indicating that the output is supported.

Enum.name: ComponentClass_1
Enum.description: ROM table.

Enum.name: ComponentClass_9
Enum.description: CoreSight component.

Enum.name: ComponentClass_15
Enum.description: PrimeCell of system component with no standardized register layout, for backward compatibility.

BitField.name: ETMPD
BitField.description: ETM power down. This bit can be used by an implementation to control if the ETM is in a low power state. This bit must be cleared by the trace software tools at the beginning of a debug session. When this bit is set to 1, writes to some registers and fields might be ignored.

BitField.name: PS
BitField.description: Port size. The ETM-M4 has no influence over the external pins used for trace. These bits are implemented but not used. On an ETM reset these bits reset to 0b001.

BitField.name: SP
BitField.description: Stall processor. The FIFOFULL output can be used to stall the processor to prevent overflow. The FIFOFULL output is only enabled when the stall processor bit is set to 1. When the bit is 0 the FIFOFULL output remains LOW at all times and the FIFO overflows if there are too many trace packets. Trace resumes without corruption once the FIFO has drained, if overflow does occur. An ETM reset sets this bit to 0.

BitField.name: BO
BitField.description: Branch output. When set to 1 all branch addresses are output, even if the branch was because of a direct branch instruction. Setting this bit enables reconstruction of the program flow without having access to the memory image of the code being executed. When this bit is set to 1, more trace data is generated, and this may affect the performance of the trace system. Information about the execution of a branch is traced regardless of the state of this bit. An ETM reset sets this bit to 0.

BitField.name: DRC
BitField.description: Debug request control. When set to 1 and the trigger event occurs, the DBGRQ output is asserted until DBGACK is observed. This enables the ARM processor to be forced into Debug state. An ETM reset sets this bit to 0.

BitField.name: ETMP
BitField.description: ETM programming. This bit must be set to 1 at the start of the ETM programming sequence. Tracing is prevented while this bit is set to 1. On an ETM reset this bit is set to b1.

BitField.name: ETMPS
BitField.description: ETM port selection. This bit can be used to control other trace components in an implementation. This bit must be set by the trace software tools to ensure that trace output is enabled from this ETM. An ETM reset sets this bit to 0.

Enum.name: ETMPS_0
Enum.description: ETMEN is LOW.

Enum.name: ETMPS_1
Enum.description: ETMEN is HIGH.

BitField.name: PM2
BitField.description: This bit is implemented but has no function. An ETM reset sets this bit to 0.

BitField.name: PM
BitField.description: These bits are implemented but have no function. An ETM reset sets these bits to 0.

BitField.name: PS3
BitField.description: This bit is implemented but has no function. An ETM reset sets this bit to 0.

BitField.name: TE
BitField.description: When set, this bit enables timestamping. An ETM reset sets this bit to 0.

BitField.name: NumberOfAddressComparatorPairs
BitField.description: Number of address comparator pairs. The value of these bits is b0000, indicating that address comparator pairs are not implemented.

BitField.name: NDVC
BitField.description: Number of data value comparators. The value of these bits is b0000, indicating that data value comparators are not implemented.

BitField.name: NMMD
BitField.description: Number of memory map decoders. The value of these bits is b00000, indicating that memory map decoder inputs are not implemented.

BitField.name: NC
BitField.description: Number of counters. The value of these bits is b001, indicating that one counter is implemented.

BitField.name: SP
BitField.description: Sequencer present. The value of this bit is 0, indicating that the sequencer is not implemented.

BitField.name: NEI
BitField.description: Number of external inputs. The value of these bits is between b000 and b010, indicating the number of external inputs, from 0 to 2, implemented in the system.

BitField.name: NEO
BitField.description: Number of external outputs. The value of these bits is b000, indicating that no external outputs are supported.

BitField.name: FFLP
BitField.description: FIFOFULL logic present. The value of this bit is 1, indicating that FIFOFULL logic is present in the ETM. To use FIFOFULL the system must also support the function, as indicated by bit [8] of ETMSCR.

BitField.name: NCIDC
BitField.description: Number of Context ID comparators. The value of these bits is b00, indicating that Context ID comparators are not implemented.

BitField.name: TSSBP
BitField.description: Trace start/stop block present. The value of this bit is 1, indicating that the Trace start/stop block is present.

BitField.name: CMA
BitField.description: Coprocessor and memory access. The value of this bit is 1, indicating that memory-mapped access to registers is supported.

BitField.name: ETMIDRP
BitField.description: The value of this bit is 1, indicating that the ETMIDR, register 0x79, is present and defines the ETM architecture version in use.

BitField.name: UOF
BitField.description: Untraced overflow flag. If set to 1, there is an overflow that has not yet been traced. This bit is cleared to 0 when either: - trace is restarted - the ETM Power Down bit, bit [0] of the ETM Control Register, 0x00, is set to 1. Note: Setting or clearing the ETM programming bit does not cause this bit to be cleared to 0.

BitField.name: Progbit
BitField.description: ETM programming bit value (Progbit). The current effective value of the ETM Programming bit (ETM Control Register bit [10]). Tou must wait for this bit to go to 1 before you start to program the ETM.

BitField.name: Status
BitField.description: Holds the current status of the trace start/stop resource. If set to 1, it indicates that a trace on address has been matched, without a corresponding trace off address match.

BitField.name: Trigger
BitField.description: Trigger bit. Set when the trigger occurs, and prevents the trigger from being output until the ETM is next programmed.

BitField.name: MaximumPortSize
BitField.description: Maximum ETM port size bits [2:0]. These bits are used in conjunction with bit [9]. The value of these bits is b001.

BitField.name: FIFOFULLsupported
BitField.description: FIFOFULL supported. The value of this bit is 1, indicating that FIFOFULL is supported. This bit is used in conjunction with bit [23] of the ETMCCR.

BitField.name: MaximumPortSize3
BitField.description: Maximum ETM port size bit [3]. This bit is used in conjunction with bits [2:0]. Its value is 0. This has no effect on the TPIU trace port.

BitField.name: PortSizeSupported
BitField.description: Port size supported. This bit reads as 1 if the currently selected port size is supported. This has no effect on the TPIU trace port.

BitField.name: PortModeSupported
BitField.description: Port mode supported. This bit reads as 1 if the currently selected port mode is supported. This has no effect on the TPIU trace port.

BitField.name: N
BitField.description: These bits give the number of supported processors minus 1. The value of these bits is b000, indicating that there is only one processor connected.

BitField.name: NoFetchComparisons
BitField.description: No Fetch comparisons. The value of this bit is 1, indicating that fetch comparisons are not implemented.

BitField.name: TraceControlEnable
BitField.description: Trace start/stop enable. The trace start/stop resource, resource 0x5F, is unaffected by the value of this bit.

Enum.name: TraceControlEnable_0
Enum.description: Tracing is unaffected by the trace start/stop logic.

Enum.name: TraceControlEnable_1
Enum.description: Tracing is controlled by the trace on and off addresses configured for the trace start/stop logic.

BitField.name: FIFOFullLevel
BitField.description: FIFO full level. The number of bytes left in FIFO, below which the FIFOFULL or SupressData signal is asserted. For example, setting this value to 15 causes data trace suppression or processor stalling, if enabled, when there are less than 15 free bytes in the FIFO.

BitField.name: ImplementationRevision
BitField.description: Implementation revision. The value of these bits is b0000, indicating implementation revision, 0.

BitField.name: MinorETMarchitectureVersion
BitField.description: Minor ETM architecture version. The value of these bits is 0b0101, indicating minor architecture version number 5.

BitField.name: MajorETMarchitectureVersion
BitField.description: Major ETM architecture version. The value of these bits is 0b0010, indicating major architecture version number 3, ETMv3.

BitField.name: ProcessorFamily
BitField.description: Processor family. The value of these bits is 0b1111, indicating that the processor family is not identified in this register.

BitField.name: LoadPCfirst
BitField.description: Load PC first. The value of this bit is 0, indicating that data tracing is not supported.

BitField.name: ThumbInstructionTracing
BitField.description: 32-bit Thumb instruction tracing. The value of this bit is 1, indicating that a 32-bit Thumb instruction is traced as a single instruction.

Enum.name: ThumbInstructionTracing_0
Enum.description: A 32-bit Thumb instruction is traced as two instructions, and exceptions might occur between these two instructions.

Enum.name: ThumbInstructionTracing_1
Enum.description: A 32-bit Thimb instruction is traced as a single instruction.

BitField.name: SecurityExtensionSupport
BitField.description: Security Extensions support. The value of this bit is 0, indicating that the ETM behaves as if the processor is in Secure state at all times.

Enum.name: SecurityExtensionSupport_0
Enum.description: The ETM behaves as if the processor is in Secure state at all times.

Enum.name: SecurityExtensionSupport_1
Enum.description: The ARM architecture Security Extensions are implemented by the processor.

BitField.name: BranchPacketEncoding
BitField.description: Branch packet encoding. The value of this bit is 1, indicating that alternative branch packet encoding is implemented.

Enum.name: BranchPacketEncoding_0
Enum.description: The ETM implements the original branch packet encoding.

Enum.name: BranchPacketEncoding_1
Enum.description: The ETM implements the alternative branch packet encoding.

BitField.name: ImplementorCode
BitField.description: Implementor code. These bits identify ARM as the implementor of the processor. The value of these bits is 01000001.

BitField.name: ExtendedExternalInputSelectors
BitField.description: Extended external input selectors. The value of these bits is 0, indicating that extended external input selectors are not implemented.

BitField.name: ExtendedExternalInputBus
BitField.description: Extended external input bus. The value of these bits is 0, indicating that the extended external input bus is not implemented.

BitField.name: ReadableRegisters
BitField.description: Readable registers. The value of this bit is 1, indicating that all registers are readable.

BitField.name: DataAddressComparisons
BitField.description: Data address comparisons. The value of this bit is 1, indicating that data address comparisons are not supported.

BitField.name: InstrumentationResources
BitField.description: Instrumentation resources. The value of these bits is 0b000, indicating that no Instrumentation resources are supported.

BitField.name: EmbeddedICEwatchpointInputs
BitField.description: EmbeddedICE watchpoint inputs. The value of these bits is 0b0100, indicating that the number of EmbeddedICE watchpoint inputs implemented is four. These inputs come from the DWT.

BitField.name: TraceStartStopBlockUsesEmbeddedICEwatchpointInputs
BitField.description: Trace Start/Stop block uses EmbeddedICE watchpoint inputs. The value of this bit is 1, indicating that the Trace Start/Stop block uses the EmbeddedICE watchpoint inputs.

BitField.name: EmbeddedICEbehaviorControlImplemented
BitField.description: EmbeddedICE behavior control implemented. The value of this bit is 0, indicating that the ETMEIBCR is not implemented.

BitField.name: TimestampingImplemented
BitField.description: Timestamping implemented. This bit is set to 1, indicating that timestamping is implemented.

BitField.name: ReducedFunctionCounter
BitField.description: Reduced function counter. Set to 1 to indicate that Counter 1 is a reduced function counter.

BitField.name: TimestampEncoding
BitField.description: Timestamp encoding. Set to 1 to indicate that the timestamp is encoded as a natural binary number.

BitField.name: TimestampSize
BitField.description: Timestamp size. Set to 0 to indicate a size of 48 bits.

BitField.name: StartResourceSelection
BitField.description: Start resource selection. Setting any of these bits to 1 selects the corresponding EmbeddedICE watchpoint input as a TraceEnable start resource. Bit [0] corresponds to input 1, bit [1] corresponds to input 2, bit [2] corresponds to input 3, and bit [3] corresponds to input 4.

BitField.name: StopResourceSelection
BitField.description: Stop resource selection. Setting any of these bits to 1 selects the corresponding EmbeddedICE watchpoint input as a TraceEnable stop resource. Bit [16] corresponds to input 1, bit [17] corresponds to input 2, bit [18] corresponds to input 3, and bit [19] corresponds to input 4.

BitField.name: TraceID
BitField.description: Trace ID to output onto the trace bus. On an ETM reset this field is cleared to 0x00.

BitField.name: ETMpoweredup
BitField.description: The value of this bit indicates whether you can access the ETM Trace Registers. The value of this bit is always 1, indicating that the ETM Trace Registers can be accessed.

BitField.name: EXTIN
BitField.description: A read of these bits returns the value of the EXTIN[1:0] input pins.

BitField.name: COREHALT
BitField.description: A read of this bit returns the value of the COREHALT input pin.

BitField.name: TRIGGER
BitField.description: A write to this bit sets the TRIGGER output.

Register.name: ETM_ITATBCTR2
Register.description: ETM Integration Test ATB Control 2 Register

BitField.name: ATREADY
BitField.description: A read of this bit returns the value of the ETM ATREADY input.

Register.name: ETM_ITATBCTR0
